OL,7,F'He didn't stab himself, did he?'JThe
OL,8,Ffollowing day Mrs Rawle was in
OL,9,Fcustody, .
OL,11,FShe claimed she had no memory of
OL,12,Finflicting the blow which killed her
OL,13,Fhusband.J"I don't remember actually
OL,14,Fholding it, but the fact is I was the
OL,15,Fonly person there, he didn't stab
OL,16,Fhimself did he?" she said.JOver the
OL,17,Fcourse of six hours of interviews, Mrs
OL,18,FRawle claimed she had been abused,
OL,19,Ftortured and sexually assaulted by her
OL,20,Fhusband.
