OL,7,FThe couple were compared to characters
OL,8,Ffrom the Roald Dahl story 'The Twits'.
OL,10,FFriends, neighbours and family members
OL,11,Fspoke in court, both in support of Mrs
OL,12,FRawle and against her. Some witnesses
OL,13,Fgave evidence from behind a screen due
OL,14,Fto the sensitivity of what they had to
OL,15,Fsay.
OL,17,FCovert video recordingsJMrs Rawle
OL,18,Fwould on her mobile phone. They would
OL,19,Frow about money, work, her health,
OL,20,Ftheir children and the state of their
OL,21,Fmarriage.
